			<p>When a young nurse takes a job in a secluded, 1970s Florida nursing home, she faces the harsh realities of caring for ailing patients. Her troubles become even greater when she learns of her superior&rsquo;s unauthorized use of morphine to relieve people&rsquo;s pain. <br />
<br />
Created by recent University of Central Florida graduate Laura Lopez, &ldquo;Acts of Mercy&rdquo; was screened this week in China at the 12th-Annual Shanghai International Film Festival. Lopez, a first-time feature director from Ecuador, worked on the film while at UCF as part of its graduate MFA program in Film &amp; Digital Media. <br />
<br />
The Shanghai screening was the world premiere of Lopez&rsquo;s unique and groundbreaking ethical thriller. The Chinese film festival runs from Saturday, June 13, through Sunday, June 21.<br />
<br />
Lopez directed, wrote and produced &ldquo;Acts of Mercy&rdquo; with a creative and technical team made up mostly of women. Producer Erica Harrell, a Cuban-American, produced her first independent feature films while working as a coordinator on HBO&rsquo;s hit television series &ldquo;Entourage.&rdquo; <br />
<br />
Harrell and Lopez met in 2004 while both were undergraduate students at UCF and kept in close contact over the years to work on the film&rsquo;s concept. <br />
<br />
Made with a small budget, &ldquo;Acts of Mercy&rdquo; was shot in 2007 in 90-degree weather at the abandoned Sunland Mental Hospital in west Orlando. The film stars two-time Emmy and four-time Tony nominee Toyah Feldshuh and up-and-coming actress Aleksa Palladino. <br />
<br />
Palladino will soon be seen in the HBO-Martin Scorsese series, &ldquo;Boardwalk Empire,&rdquo; while Feldshuh is currently performing as Irene Gupty in her Broadway hit show, &ldquo;Irena&rsquo;s Vow.&ldquo;<br />
<br />
Lopez graduated from UCF&rsquo;s three-year Entrepreneurial Digital Cinema MFA track in 2008. She began her career as an intern at several prestigious production companies, including Kennedy Marshall, Red Wagon and Jerry Weintraub productions. Shortly after, she worked for a daytime Spanish-speaking television series based out of Burbank, Calif. <br />
<br />
Lopez has directed several short-form documentary and narrative films. She resides in Orlando, where she develops new projects for her production company, Ambrosia Films.<br />
<br />
To learn more about &ldquo;Acts of Mercy,&rdquo; visit <a href="http://www.actsofmercymovie.com">http://www.actsofmercymovie.com</a>.<br />
<br />
To read about UCF&rsquo;s MFA in Film and Digital Media and other student success stories, go to <a href="http://www.film.ucf.edu">http://www.film.ucf.edu</a>.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>UCF Stands For Opportunity</strong>: The University of Central Florida is a metropolitan research university that ranks as the 5th largest in the nation with more than 50,000 students. UCF's first classes were offered in 1968. The university offers impressive academic and research environments that power the region's economic development. UCF's culture of opportunity is driven by our diversity, Orlando environment, history of entrepreneurship and our youth, relevance and energy. For more information visit <a href="http://www.news.ucf.edu/">http://www.news.ucf.edu</a>.</p>
		
	
